6.1  Air $( N _ { 2 } , O _ { 2 } , C O , C O _ { 2 } )$ and Oxygen — This procedure is for the determination of air components in octafluorocyclobutane using a gas chromatograph with a discharge ionization detector.  Column switching is used to separate and elute the components and to backflush octafluorocyclobutane.  One method/column is used for $\Nu _ { 2 }$ , $\mathrm { O } _ { 2 }$ , and CO and a second method/column is used for $\mathrm { C O } _ { 2 }$ .  The sample should be taken from the vapor in the container directly into the instrument sampling system.  The container being analyzed should have equilibrated at approximately $3 0 ^ { \circ } \mathrm { C }$ before analysis is begun.  
6.1.1  Detection Limits  — Nitrogen,  10 ppb vol;
Oxygen,  50 ppb vol;  Carbon monoxide,  10 ppb vol;
Carbon dioxide,  10 ppb vol.
